node.text:
…I am forever grateful to the 43 souls who embarked on this journey with me. We arrived as strangers, but we left as family. So much healing took place—physically, emotionally, mentally, and spiritually. 💞
•
The #retreat week was filled with delicious #rawvegan meals, #fitness, #wellness classes, breath-work, meditation, fun, and so much more! It was a celebration of life and connection. ⛵️🎉✨
•
Special thank you to @jasem.ashkanani for creating this INSANE video. You really outdid yourself with this one!!! 🎥🙏🏽🎞 Thank you again to @rawchefalicia and all of the chefs and teams at @jademountainstlucia and @ansechastanet for hosting us at your resort and helping to make this event possible.
•
No future retreat dates have been set. If you’re interested in a future announcement, please sign-up for my email newsletter at www.FullyRaw.com. The link is in profile. 📲💞 For more shares and updates, please follow my @fullyrawretreats page as well. 💫
•
I can’t say or share ENOUGH about this incredible week. It was life-changing for all of us. ☀️🌈💫
•

Whether you are looking to connect with other like-minded individuals, learn about plant-based foods, or even just enjoy a healthy vacation...this retreat is a once-in-a-lifetime luxury experience. There are only 30 spots for this intimate retreat, so do not wait to book. There are less than 10 spots remaining. Please read through our website page to see all of the details, information, and itinerary. For serious inquiries, please email retreats@fullyraw.com or simply reserve your spot on the checkout page. Thank you, and I hope to be able to host you in St. Lucia for a magical retreat experience!

For covid precautions, you can check out the www.jademountain.com website to see what measures they have in place for your well-being.

Those who know me, know that I love with my @pranamat. The benefits of these sets are so helpful I gifted one to all of my retreat attendees in 2019! The @pranamat is an acupressure and massage set that helps to relieve tension, reduce stress, release back pain, tone skin, and increase circulation.
•
For all my followers, I have the promo code: KRISTINA20 - it gives you 20% off everything! ✨💝✨
•
While there are so many ways to use this set, here are 5 different ways that I am showing you today...
•
1️⃣ Step on it! Give your feet a little massage. The lotus flowers touch all the pressure points on your foot, and in my opinion, this experience is better than getting a reflexology foot massage.
2️⃣ Sit on your thigh or IT band. This helps to loosen and strengthen those side leg muscles, and it also helps to tone the skin by bringing more circulation and by activating the skin and tissues.
3️⃣ Sit on it! Give your booty a little invigoration. Trust me when I say this one is intense!
4️⃣ Place the pillow under your lower-back or underneath your stomach. Stretching over the pillow is one of the best ways to release that intense lower back pain. If you're having tummy issues or simply want to help your digestion, place the pillow under your stomach and breath slowly and deeply.
5️⃣ Lay bare on your back. I recommend for beginners to use a t-shirt.
•
15-20 minutes on your set is all that it takes to experience the benefits and relief of this acupressure set. The whole set is made from the best quality sustainable hemp. It's vegan and eco-friendly and is OEKO-Tex certified.
•
20% off code: KRISTINA20
•
Enjoy my friends! 😘

Therefore, the things I am focusing on more for myself are the following:

🦋 More active listening and less speaking.

🦋 Focusing on how to create more unity instead of division.

🦋 Showing up as an EMBODIMENT of love.
•
As so many of us are doing our best to navigate these challenging times, I think what’s important is seeking understanding, having whole-hearted discussions, creating leadership, and fostering CONNECTION. 🙏🏽🌿💫
•
I personally don’t desire to live in an echo-chamber. I want to be open to growth and healing. I believe this is where real change happens. 🌙
•
We are all better as individuals when we are connected with others—as well as with ourselves. 🌗
•
I’m not sure where you’re at in your journey, but if I can encourage you to do one thing, it would be to BRING LOVE to the table in every given moment.
•
Let grace guide you. ☀️🌊💫
Love you. 🌸💗✨
•

👗 @flookthelabel

node.text:
HAPPY 98th BIRTHDAY JÊDDO! 🥳💫 I have the best grandpa in the entire world. God has blessed our family with the BEST role model. We have a huge Lebanese family, and he’s always the voice of positivity and force of good, no matter what is happening. He’s my hero. 🍉✨
•
They don’t make men like Jêddo anymore. My grandpa served in WW2, and he’s always been SO proud of it. As a Lebanese immigrant, he’s never taken his freedom lightly. He used to sell shoes and newspapers on the street when he was only 7 years old, and he has worked his ENTIRE life to achieve his dreams. He STILL goes to work everyday at 98-years of age. He believes it keeps his mind sharp. 👈🏽 He’s been through so much—3x cancer survivor, COVID survivor, survived the Great Depression, went to law school then got into real estate, married to my Nana for nearly 70 years...the list goes on and on...it just shows how much a person can accomplish in a lifetime…and he’s STILL going strong. 😭
•
He is absolutely the most wonderful human and amazing man. Writing captions for him literally makes me cry. 98 years of life is more than a celebration…it’s a gift. 🎁 He’s one of a kind. ♥️😩♥️
•
I am not with him today, but I know he’s surrounded by family right now. We’ve been FaceTiming. I’ll hopefully be able to see him in-person soon. Who knows, maybe he will come to Hawaii soon. The time we get to enjoy together is absolute happiness. ♥️ 
•
Thank you God. 🙏🏽
•
Love you Jêddo. You’re my forever hero. ♥️🥰🍉
•
#grandpa #family #birthday #vegan #plantbased #specialmoments #dancing #happybirthday

node.text:
I’ve spent years working on my own physical and personal development. Now I’m invested in my emotional and spiritual protection. 🌹 No matter which way you spin it, there are multiple warfares happening right now. We cannot show up in the world as leaders without having discernment, compassion, and strength. Therefore, I am focusing on creating safe spaces for myself and nurturing what’s good for my soul. 👈🏽 Honoring our needs and having the courage to love others and ourselves despite any criticisms or judgements isn’t easy, but I believe it’s where the real growth happens. 🌿
•
Some people will apologize and say, “I’m sorry I haven’t been myself lately.” I’m going to say the opposite. I’ve been so MUCH of myself that I am sometimes at a loss for knowing how to translate that energy to this space and share what’s on my heart. ✨🌕🌊✨
•
I used to be so open and vulnerable in this space—sharing every aspect of my life’s journey with you. After dealing with so much hate and harassment, it’s caused me to go inward to reflect on how I can better share my journey with others, or perhaps, how can my experiences help pull others through dark times. ✨🌓✨
•
It’s beautiful to go inward and face those darker parts within us. It’s how we find ourselves. 🕯🥀
•
I’ve never felt more at home in my skin than I do in this moment.
•
My foremost priority has been to teach myself the art of healthy boundaries, self-preservation, and personal peace. 🕊
•
I’ve grown and matured a lot, and with every experience that has shaped me, I’ve learned to be more selective and protective of my inner peace as well as any information that people could use to create pain. My focus remains with finding solutions to foster wellness and with loving as deeply as I can. 🐛🦋🐠
•
After all thats transpired, I choose to use my mind and soul as vessel of love. ♥️
•
People will only see what they want to see. We must keep showing up with as much conviction as we can. Love will always win if we continue to choose love. 👈🏽
•
May each of us choose to be a vessel of love. 🙏🏽
•
We’ve got this. Let’s keep moving forward. ♥️ #fullyraw #wordstoliveby #vegan #healing

How to grow your own microgreens at home for 49¢ a day! Easy start-to-finish mini-tutorial. 🌱 A new YouTube video has just been uploaded to my channel sharing with you a complete guide for beginners to growing your own microgreens with tons of health tips and money saving tips, so be sure to watch to the end! 🥳
•
The benefits of #growing your own food are ENDLESS. Not only is it absolutely wonderful for your #health to consume more fresh #greens in your diet, but also growing your own food, even simple foods such as #sprouts or microgreens, can be one of the most cost-effective ways to consume a ton of nutrients, phytonutrients, and minerals on a daily basis. So many of you have reached out to me and said that you wish you could grow your own food, but don’t have the means or space. The solution: you can #grow your own microgreens at home in simple trays that you can keep on your countertops. Growing your own #microgreens is simple and easy. It requires minimal equipment. My intention is to show you how to grow your own food with very little no matter where you are or how much space you have. You can grow microgreens or even sprouts no matter where you live. No special lighting required.
•
Microgreens can take anywhere from 9-14 days to grow fully. The final trays I’m holding are 12 days old.
•
Where can you get the best seeds, and what #seeds do I use? @trueleafmarket is the BEST. I use their seeds for EVERYTHING. They are #organic and #nonGMO. I don’t compromise on #gardening quality, and they have the best prices as well. Check out the link in my bio to start ordering your seeds now. 🌱
•
All the links you need are in my bio! Enjoy my friends! ☀️🥬🥒💫 #fullyraw #vegan #garden

LAZY RAW FOOD DINNER IDEAS 🌱🥑🍅💫 You MUST try one of these four simple, satisfying, savory, and delicious recipes! Save this post for a day when you don’t feel like preparing a fancy meal. These dishes take under 15 minutes to make…and will make your taste buds explode with flavor! 🥰 Gotta eat the rainbow! 🌈🌱🌟
•
The following recipes include:
🥑 Chunky guacamole wraps with fresh sprouts
🌈 Rainbow crudités with a creamy ranch dip
🥒 Simple cucumber avocado soup with dehydrated raw crackers
🥭 Mango pineapple gazpacho for the win!
•
A #YouTube video is up on my channel @fullyrawkristina sharing the complete makings of each meal. Go to www.YouTube.com/FullyRawKristina (link in profile)…please check it out! 🤩🙏🏽
✨
These exact recipes have been added to my #FullyRaw #vegan #app for you. Get access to these recipes along with 450+ other #plantpowered recipes. 🥳  My #recipe app is now FREE to download on both iTunes or Google Play, and once you download it you can choose a monthly or yearly subscription plan. The #recipes on my app are #rawvegan,  #healthy, #delicious, and #plantbased. Please download it and enjoy! 👈🏽

Just a girl and her pup making waves in Hawaii 🐶🌊☀️ It’s not the best phone pic, but after Cash snapped it in the moment, I realized how special these moments ARE. Cherish your loved ones and spend time with them. THESE are the moments that matter the most. 🙏🏽💫 
•
If you would have asked me years ago when I was going through one of the most devastating times of my life where I would end up today…I most likely wouldn’t have told you that I’d end up on an island with my rescue @fullyrawkoko living on a farm installing a fruit orchard. That’s how life works sometimes. You learn to enjoy the journey. I’m grateful for all the growth opportunities of the past, present, and future. 🏝🌺
•
Much love to you all. I hope you’re having a wonderful weekend. 🌈☀️💫 #fullyraw #vegan #rescue #hawaii #hike #islandlife
